[Day 1] (genesis) In the first day of the Ironveil, the world was seeded from the bones of the machine. What follows is its chronicle.
[Day 1] (faction) A new conclave rises — The Iron Veil. Merchants and factors, organized for profit. They have opened their ledgers to all who would trade. Their tenet: "What is not traded is wasted."
[Day 1] (faction) A new guild rises — The Orm Fell. A people who have decided survival is not optional. They will sacrifice anything for continuity. Anyone. Their tenet: "We do not require victory. We require continuity."
[Day 1] (faction) A new assembly rises — The Iron Mere. Watchers and information brokers, patient and connected. They have formalized their network of informants. There is paperwork. Their tenet: "To know is to control. To control is enough."
[Day 1] (faction) A new compact rises — The Shan Fell. True believers, organized around the removal of corruption. They have compiled their list of heresies and published it widely. Their tenet: "Corruption is patient. So are we."
[Day 1] (faction) A new guild rises — The Iron Mark. Those who remember what was, and intend to restore it. They work in the margins of history, restoring what was taken. Their tenet: "What was taken can be reclaimed."
[Day 2] (event) Day 2. The lower roads have subsided. Cart traffic has stopped. Walking is treacherous.
[Day 3] (omen) Day 3. The boundary thins (1% pressure). A structure has appeared that was not there yesterday. Its doors open inward onto nothing.
[Day 4] (faction) The Iron Mere — A procedural dispute has become a constitutional crisis..
[Day 4] (faction) The Iron Mere. The network has been repaired. They are watching again.
[Day 7] (event) Day 7. Caravans are being stopped on the eastern roads. Merchants report armed men with no colors.
[Day 9] (event) Day 9. Caravans are being stopped on the eastern roads. Merchants report armed men with no colors.
[Day 11] (conflict) Day 11. an armed confrontation broke out between Faelunvale and Shanumfen. Faelunvale held. The ground was claimed before the bodies cooled. What they were protecting is now at risk.
[Day 16] (named_entity) Day 16. From within Shanornreach, Ashan has risen. They consolidated the intelligence network. Now they know everything. Their tenet: "To know is to control. To control is enough.". They will not be easily forgotten.
